The paper deals with a general problem that encompasses many frequently asked questions in various areas of computer science, including constraint satisfaction, databases, matrix operations, probabilistic graphical models, and logic. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, such as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, given the focus on constraint programming and graphical model inference, as well as the use of dynamic programming and worst-case analysis techniques, cs.DS and cs.AI seem to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DB, and cs.CC.
